<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="981" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d981">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14084a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 26, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>376. Press despatches announce that the Provisional President has issued
                            an order directing, generals to abstain from summary executions. The
                            President heartily approves the action taken. Please convey this
                            information to General Gutiérrez and if you consider the circumstances
                            favorable urge upon Villa acceptance of this order as best means of
                            strengthening Provisional Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>